      • addNeighbour

        public boolean addNeighbour​(int key,
                            int weight)
        Adds a vertex key to map of neighbours, assumes that the key represents an existing vertex. Assigns weight to the added vertex from weight parameter.
        Parameters:
        key - a vertex key.
        weight - an integer number to represent the weight of an edge.
        Returns:
        True if vertex was added as neighbour, false if already a neighbour.

      • addNeighbour

        public boolean addNeighbour​(int key,
                            int weight,
                            int accessible)
        Adds a vertex key to map of neighbours, assumes that the key represents an existing vertex. Assigns weight to the added vertex from weight parameter. Assigns accessible status from accessible parameter.
        Parameters:
        key - a vertex key.
        weight - an integer number to represent the weight of an edge.
        accessible - integer value for accessible status; 0 for not accessible 1 for accessible.
        Returns:
        True if vertex was added as neighbour, false if already a neighbour.
